<task id="012" project="email-communication-solution-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>RecipientField sub-component — canonical To/Cc/Bcc with separator parsing + directory autocomplete</title>
    <phase>Wave 1 — Engine + Wrappers + Sub-Components</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>5</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>011</dependencies>
    <blocks>020, 028</blocks>
    <tags>react, frontend, fluent-ui, communication</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Replaces 5 distinct recipient-normalization implementations identified in the driver assessment; canonical UX for every email surface; ADR-021 (Fluent v9) + NFR-09 (a11y) + paste-from-Outlook compatibility (separator parsing) are load-bearing user-facing concerns. FULL guards against regressions across all migrating callers.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>C</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <fr-refs>FR-05</fr-refs>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Build the single canonical `<RecipientField />` sub-component at `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/EmailComposer/subcomponents/RecipientField.tsx`. One implementation, three use sites (To / Cc / Bcc) — replaces 5 different recipient-normalization implementations identified in the assessment.

    Requirements (FR-05):
    - Accepts string-with-`;`-or-`,`-separator input (paste-from-Outlook compatibility — Outlook copies addresses separated by `; `)
    - On commit (Enter, Tab, blur, or separator key), parse the string into individual addresses
    - Each parsed address resolves via `searchUsersAndContacts()` directory autocomplete (existing service in `@spaarke/ui-components`)
    - Resolved entries render as Fluent `&lt;Tag /&gt;` chips with displayName + remove-X button
    - Unresolved-but-valid email-format addresses render as plain-text Tag chips (no directory metadata)
    - Invalid email format on commit → reject (don't add as Tag), surface validation error via parent's reducer dispatch
    - Component is controlled: receives `value: IRecipient[]` and `onChange(IRecipient[])` from engine reducer
    - Keyboard nav: arrow keys between Tags, Backspace removes last Tag, Tab moves focus out of field
    - Screen-reader: `aria-label="To recipients"` / `Cc recipients` / `Bcc recipients` based on `label` prop

    Files:
    - `subcomponents/RecipientField.tsx` (NEW)
    - `subcomponents/RecipientField.types.ts` (NEW — `IRecipient { displayName: string; email: string; type: 'user' | 'contact' | 'unknown'; entityRef?: { entityName: string; recordId: string } }`)
    - Update `EmailComposer.types.ts` to import `IRecipient` from this file (or move to a shared types module)
    - Update `EmailComposer/index.ts` to export `RecipientField` + `IRecipient`
  </prompt>

  <role>
    React + Fluent UI v9 developer with a11y experience. Familiar with Fluent v9 `&lt;Combobox /&gt;` / `&lt;Tag /&gt;` / `&lt;TagGroup /&gt;` primitives and the controlled-component pattern.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `&lt;RecipientField /&gt;` component compiles, lint-clean, renders correctly in the engine slots. Paste-from-Outlook test: `"Alice &lt;alice@example.com&gt;; Bob &lt;bob@example.com&gt;"` parses into 2 Tags. Directory autocomplete: typing `"al"` triggers `searchUsersAndContacts('al')` and shows dropdown. Validation: typing `"notanemail"` + Enter → rejected, validation error dispatched. Keyboard nav functional (Tab, Backspace, arrows). `npm run build` + `npm run lint` clean.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Driver assessment identified 5 different recipient-normalization implementations across email surfaces — each parsed `;` / `,` separators differently, validated emails differently, and rendered Tags differently. Result: inconsistent UX + occasional duplicate-Tag bugs. This component is the single canonical implementation.

      `searchUsersAndContacts()` already exists in `@spaarke/ui-components/src/services/` — used by other autocomplete contexts. It returns `{ users: User[]; contacts: Contact[] }` from Dataverse + Graph (per existing implementation; reuse the existing signature).

      Tags vs plain-text Tags: a "resolved" recipient has a `entityRef` (user / contact GUID) — useful for downstream `sprk_communication.sprk_to_collection` polymorphic stamping. Unresolved but valid emails (e.g., external addresses not in the directory) render as plain-text Tags and still send successfully (they end up as email-only entries in the request body).
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/EmailComposer/subcomponents/RecipientField.tsx (NEW)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/EmailComposer/subcomponents/RecipientField.types.ts (NEW)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/EmailComposer/EmailComposer.types.ts (UPDATE — import IRecipient)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/EmailComposer/index.ts (UPDATE — export RecipientField, IRecipient)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/services/ (READ — find searchUsersAndContacts())</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Fluent UI v9 only — use `&lt;Combobox /&gt;`, `&lt;Tag /&gt;`, `&lt;TagGroup /&gt;`, `&lt;Field /&gt;` from `@fluentui/react-components`</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">No direct `@spaarke/auth` import — `searchUsersAndContacts()` already takes `authenticatedFetch` parameter (per NFR-02 decoupling rule); pass it through from engine props</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-033">Canonical impl — DO NOT clone existing recipient implementations; this REPLACES them</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-09">Full keyboard nav (Tab, arrow, Backspace, Enter); `aria-label` based on `label` prop; live region for validation errors handled by parent (task 020)</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Component is CONTROLLED — `value: IRecipient[]` + `onChange(IRecipient[])`; never holds its own state for recipients (engine reducer owns state)</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Commit on: Enter, Tab, `;`/`,` keystroke, or blur — all four trigger the parse-and-resolve flow</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Paste support: `onPaste` event handler parses pasted text via the same separator logic before commit</constraint>
  </constraints>

