  <steps>
    <step order="1">Grep for `searchUsersAndContacts` in `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/services/` to confirm signature + `authenticatedFetch` parameter shape.</step>
    <step order="2">Author `RecipientField.types.ts` with `IRecipient` shape per prompt.</step>
    <step order="3">Author `RecipientField.tsx`:
      - Props: `{ label: 'To' | 'Cc' | 'Bcc'; value: IRecipient[]; onChange: (next: IRecipient[]) =&gt; void; onValidationError?: (code: string, message: string) =&gt; void; authenticatedFetch: typeof fetch }`
      - Local state ONLY for the input buffer (text being typed) — NOT for the resolved Tags
      - Separator parse: `const parseAddresses = (input: string): string[] =&gt; input.split(/[;,]/).map(s =&gt; s.trim()).filter(Boolean)`
      - Email regex validation (RFC 5322 simplified): `/^[^\s@]+@[^\s@]+\.[^\s@]+$/`
      - Commit handler: parse, validate each, resolve via `searchUsersAndContacts` (best-effort — if directory lookup fails, fall back to email-only Tag), call `onChange` with new union
      - Render `&lt;Field label={label}&gt;&lt;TagGroup&gt;...&lt;/TagGroup&gt;&lt;Combobox /&gt;&lt;/Field&gt;`</step>
    <step order="4">Update `EmailComposer.types.ts` to re-export `IRecipient` from `subcomponents/RecipientField.types`.</step>
    <step order="5">Update `EmailComposer/index.ts` to export `RecipientField` and the `IRecipient` type.</step>
    <step order="6">Smoke test in dev: paste `"Alice &lt;alice@example.com&gt;; bob@example.com,charlie@example.com"` → 3 Tags; type `"not"` → no autocomplete results; Enter → rejected; Backspace → last Tag removed.</step>
    <step order="7">Run `npm run build` + `npm run lint` — both clean.</step>
    <step order="7.5">Step 9.5 quality gates — invoke `code-review` + `adr-check` (ADR-021, ADR-028).</step>
    <step order="8">Update `TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 012 ✅.</step>
    <step order="9">Update `current-task.md` per task-execute protocol.</step>
  </steps>

